

// =========================
// 1. public Folder
// =========================


The public folder is used to serve static files directly to the browser.

Examples:

HTML files
CSS files
JavaScript files
Images (.jpg, .png, .svg)
Videos
Fonts



app.use(express.static("public"));(CSS, JS, Images serve karne ke liye)

Route → Controller → res.sendFile() or fs.readFile() (HTML serve karne ke liye)


Folder Structure:

project/
│
├── public/
│   ├── css/
│   │   └── style.css
│   ├── js/
│   │   └── script.js
│   └── images/
│       └── logo.png




// =========================
// 
//   2. views Folder
// =========================


The views folder contains template files that are rendered by Express using a template engine.

Common template engines:

EJS (.ejs)
Pug (.pug)
Handlebars (.hbs)

Example:

project/
│
├── views/
│   ├── home.ejs
│   └── about.ejs

Route:

app.set("view engine", "ejs");

app.get("/", (req, res) => {
    res.render("home");
});




// =========================
// 3.genrating a absolute path dynamically
// =========================

path.join(__dirname, ...) to generate the absolute path dynamically.